<li id="cite_note-85"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-85">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWinter1889" class="citation news cs1">Winter, Arthur (June 3, 1889). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/digital/collection/MStar/id/18361">"Discourse Delivered by President Wilford Woodruff at the General Conference, Salt Lake City, on Sunday Afternoon, April 7, 1877"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Millennial_Star" title="Millennial Star">Millennial Star</a></i>. Vol.&#160;51, no.&#160;22. Liverpool, England. p.&#160;339 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>. <q>[T]hat mark of darkness still rest upon [the descendants of Cain]. ... The Lamanites, on this continent, suffered a similar experience. ... [T]he Lord put a curse of redness upon them. Hundreds of years have passed since then, but wherever you meet the Lamanites to-day, you see that mark upon them.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Millennial+Star&amp;rft.atitle=Discourse+Delivered+by+President+Wilford+Woodruff+at+the+General+Conference%2C+Salt+Lake+City%2C+on+Sunday+Afternoon%2C+April+7%2C+1877.&amp;rft.volume=51&amp;rft.issue=22&amp;rft.pages=339&amp;rft.date=1889-06-03&amp;rft.aulast=Winter&amp;rft.aufirst=Arthur&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fcontentdm.lib.byu.edu%2Fdigital%2Fcollection%2FMStar%2Fid%2F18361&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
