<li id="cite_note-Balmer-88"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Balmer_88-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBalmerRiess2015" class="citation book cs1">Balmer, Randall; <a href="/wiki/Jana_Riess" title="Jana Riess">Riess, Jana</a> (December 8, 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=mQ7TCgAAQBAJ"><i>Mormonism and American Politics</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/Columbia_University_Press" title="Columbia University Press">Columbia University Press</a>. p.&#160;168. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-231-54089-6" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-231-54089-6"><bdi>978-0-231-54089-6</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormonism+and+American+Politics&amp;rft.pages=168&amp;rft.pub=Columbia+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2015-12-08&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-231-54089-6&amp;rft.aulast=Balmer&amp;rft.aufirst=Randall&amp;rft.au=Riess%2C+Jana&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DmQ7TCgAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Image-89"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Image_89-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Image_89-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFReynolds1868" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/George_Reynolds_(Mormon)" title="George Reynolds (Mormon)">Reynolds, George</a> (November 15, 1868). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/juvenileinstruct322geor/page/173/mode/1up">"Man and His Varieties: Food-Habits-Religion, Etc"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Juvenile_Instructor" class="mw-redirect" title="The Juvenile Instructor">The Juvenile Instructor</a></i>. <b>3</b> (22): 173 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>For the day will come ... when all men will lose their extravagances of character and appearance, and become 'a white and delightsome people' physically as well as morally. When they will be as God first made Adam 'in his own image' and 'very good.'<span class="cs1-kern-right"></span></q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Juvenile+Instructor&amp;rft.atitle=Man+and+His+Varieties%3A+Food-Habits-Religion%2C+Etc.&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.issue=22&amp;rft.pages=173&amp;rft.date=1868-11-15&amp;rft.aulast=Reynolds&amp;rft.aufirst=George&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fjuvenileinstruct322geor%2Fpage%2F173%2Fmode%2F1up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-kidd-90"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-kidd_90-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKidd2006" class="citation book cs1">Kidd, Colin (2006). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=aNT3q1HjY_MC&amp;pg=PA236"><i>The Forging of Races: Race and Scripture in the Protestant Atlantic World, 1600–2000</i></a>. Cambridge, England: <a href="/wiki/Cambridge_University_Press" title="Cambridge University Press">Cambridge University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-521-79324-7" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-521-79324-7"><bdi>978-0-521-79324-7</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Forging+of+Races%3A+Race+and+Scripture+in+the+Protestant+Atlantic+World%2C+1600%E2%80%932000&amp;rft.place=Cambridge%2C+England&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-521-79324-7&amp;rft.aulast=Kidd&amp;rft.aufirst=Colin&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DaNT3q1HjY_MC%26pg%3DPA236&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-91"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-91">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFReynolds1868" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/George_Reynolds_(Mormon)" title="George Reynolds (Mormon)">Reynolds, George</a> (October 15, 1868). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/juvenileinstruct320geor/page/157/mode/1up">"Man and His Varieties: The Negro Race"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Juvenile_Instructor" class="mw-redirect" title="The Juvenile Instructor">The Juvenile Instructor</a></i>. <b>3</b> (20): 157 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>We understand that when God made man in his own image and pronounced him very good, that he made him white. We have no record of any of God's favored servants being of a black race. All His prophets and apostles belonged to the most handsome race on the face of the earth .... In this race was born His Son Jesus, who, we are told was very lovely, and 'in the express image of his Father's person, and every angel who ever brought a message of God's mercy to man was beautiful to look upon, clad in the purest white and with a countenance bright as the noonday sun.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Juvenile+Instructor&amp;rft.atitle=Man+and+His+Varieties%3A+The+Negro+Race&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.issue=20&amp;rft.pages=157&amp;rft.date=1868-10-15&amp;rft.aulast=Reynolds&amp;rft.aufirst=George&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fjuvenileinstruct320geor%2Fpage%2F157%2Fmode%2F1up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-US_Commission_1959-92"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-US_Commission_1959_92-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=zKIHERHQKBcC&amp;q=%22The+Mormon+interpretation+attributes+birth+into+any+race+other+than+the+white+%22+commission&amp;pg=PA379">"The National Conference and the Reports of the State Advisory Committees to the U.S. Commission on Civil Rights"</a>. Washington D.C.: <a href="/wiki/United_States_Government_Publishing_Office" title="United States Government Publishing Office">United States Government Publishing Office</a>. 1959. pp.&#160;379–380 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>The Mormon interpretation attributes birth into any race other than the white race as a result of inferior performance in a pre-earth life and teaches that by righteous living, the dark-skinned races may again become "white and delightsome." This doctrine is mentioned in passing by way of explaining certain attitudes evident in specific fields of investigation.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+National+Conference+and+the+Reports+of+the+State+Advisory+Committees+to+the+U.S.+Commission+on+Civil+Rights&amp;rft.place=Washington+D.C.&amp;rft.pages=379-380&amp;rft.pub=United+States+Government+Publishing+Office&amp;rft.date=1959&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DzKIHERHQKBcC%26q%3D%2522The%2BMormon%2Binterpretation%2Battributes%2Bbirth%2Binto%2Bany%2Brace%2Bother%2Bthan%2Bthe%2Bwhite%2B%2522%2Bcommission%26pg%3DPA379&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Bush_Jr.-93"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Bush_Jr._93-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBush_Jr.2001" class="citation journal cs1">Bush Jr., Lester E. (2001). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.2307%2F45226775">"Mormonism's Negro Doctrine: An Historical Overview"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue</a></i>. <b>34</b> (1/2). Champaign, Illinois: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>: 255–56. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.2307%2F45226775">10.2307/45226775</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/45226775">45226775</a>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:160186973">160186973</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Dialogue&amp;rft.atitle=Mormonism%27s+Negro+Doctrine%3A+An+Historical+Overview&amp;rft.volume=34&amp;rft.issue=1%2F2&amp;rft.pages=255-56&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A160186973%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F45226775%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F45226775&amp;rft.aulast=Bush+Jr.&amp;rft.aufirst=Lester+E.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.2307%252F45226775&am