<li id="cite_note-Race-108"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Race_108-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Race_108-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMueller2017" class="citation book cs1">Mueller, Max Perry (September 11, 2017). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=hB8wDwAAQBAJ"><i>Race and the Making of the Mormon People</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_North_Carolina_Press" title="University of North Carolina Press">University of North Carolina Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-4696-3375-6" title="Special:BookSources/978-1-4696-3375-6"><bdi>978-1-4696-3375-6</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Race+and+the+Making+of+the+Mormon+People&amp;rft.pub=University+of+North+Carolina+Press&amp;rft.date=2017-09-11&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-4696-3375-6&amp;rft.aulast=Mueller&amp;rft.aufirst=Max+Perry&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DhB8wDwAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-109"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-109">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><sup id="cite_ref-107" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-107">&#91;107&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Mueller_16-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Mueller-16">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup><sup class="reference nowrap">&#58;&#8202;<span title="Pages: 218–219&#10;Quotation: &quot;Such unions would join together the two most favored Israelite bloodlines, the (mostly white) progeny of Ephraim and the (mostly red) sons and daughters of Manasseh. Such unions would also help civilize the Indians so that they could fulfill The Book of Mormon precedent to become &#39;white, delightsome, and just.&#39; &#39;We will have intermarriages with Indians,&#39; Brigham Young purportedly taught, so &#39;the curse of their color shall be removed, and they be restored to their pristine beauty.&#39; The creation of covenants—in this case marriage covenants—between white Latter-day Saints of &#39;chosen seed&#39; and the Native American descendants of the lost tribes of Israel was the fulfillment of Book of Mormon prophecy.&quot;" class="tooltip tooltip-dashed" style="border-bottom: 1px dashed;">218–219</span>&#8202;</sup><sup id="cite_ref-Race_108-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Race-108">&#91;108&#93;</a></sup><sup class="reference nowrap"><span title="Page / location: 145">&#58;&#8202;145&#8202;</span></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-relations-110"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-relations_110-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-relations_110-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrooks1944" class="citation journal cs1">Brooks, Juanita (1944). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://scholarlypublishingcollective.org/uip/uhq/article-pdf/12/1-2/1/1380413/45058004.pdf">"Indian relations on the Mormon frontier"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/Utah_Historical_Quarterly" title="Utah Historical Quarterly">Utah Historical Quarterly</a></i>. <b>12</b> (1–2). <a href="/wiki/Utah_State_Historical_Society" title="Utah State Historical Society">Utah State Historical Society</a>: 1–48. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.2307%2F45058004">10.2307/45058004</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/45058004">45058004</a>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:254439832">254439832</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220323210844/https://watermark.silverchair.com/45058004.pdf?token=AQECAHi208BE49Ooan9kkhW_Ercy7Dm3ZL_9Cf3qfKAc485ysgAAAswwggLIBgkqhkiG9w0BBwagggK5MIICtQIBADCCAq4GCSqGSIb3DQEHATAeBglghkgBZQMEAS4wEQQMXiPkRiGJEwUXPYtEAgEQgIICf_c-IGG7CKZJQNcjhg_E3mTlhGfsNPITa2L3xRZfqS-TL4atfdxMb5s6hEcW1h55f1UmfaxaG9Z32-zBWCeaB-5YQBTVvltdbdMaGYmVJ_3UxjTn-JtcKFzH3uuUNDh3r9shm0B4CXCOgW8OINGkL7leLbXMjxZ-lV8GsGfPOdY0jSukDUdCJ9Gohv8n-Zm-HTJyhHB_LpHnidTwM0GbYf2ikbpaReygY