<li id="cite_note-113"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-113">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFVan_Leer1996" class="citation news cs1">Van Leer, Twila (March 12, 1996). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.deseretnews.com/article/476907/CHIEF-PRAISED-BY-INDIANS-WHITES-ALIKE.html">"Chief Praised By Indians Whites Alike"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Deseret_News" title="Deseret News">Deseret News</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">October 12,</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Deseret+News&amp;rft.atitle=Chief+Praised+By+Indians+Whites+Alike&amp;rft.date=1996-03-12&amp;rft.aulast=Van+Leer&amp;rft.aufirst=Twila&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deseretnews.com%2Farticle%2F476907%2FCHIEF-PRAISED-BY-INDIANS-WHITES-ALIKE.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Kimball1982-114"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Kimball1982_114-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKimball1982" class="citation book cs1">Kimball, Edward L. (1982). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=TA6QAAAAMAAJ"><i>The Teachings of Spencer W. Kimball</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. p.&#160;226. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-88494-472-7" title="Special:BookSources/0-88494-472-7"><bdi>0-88494-472-7</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>Cultural differences pose dangers for marriage. When I said you must teach your people to overcome their prejudices and accept the Indians, I did not mean that you would encourage intermarriage. I mean that they should be brothers, to worship together and to work together and to play together; but we must discourage intermarriage, not because it is sin. I would like to make this very emphatic. A couple has not committed sin if an Indian boy and a white girl are married, or vice versa. It isn't a transgression like the transgressions of which many are guilty. But it is not expedient. Marriage statistics and our general experience convince us that marriage is not easy.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Teachings+of+Spencer+W.+Kimball&amp;rft.pages=226&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1982&amp;rft.isbn=0-88494-472-7&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+L.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DTA6QAAAAMAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Slack2013-115"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Slack2013_115-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFFletcher_Stack2013" class="citation news cs1"><a href="/wiki/Peggy_Fletcher_Stack" title="Peggy Fletcher Stack">Fletcher Stack, Peggy</a> (December 16, 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://archive.sltrib.com/article.php?id=57241071&amp;itype=CMSID">"Mormon church traces black priesthood ban to Brigham Young"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Salt_Lake_Tribune" class="mw-redirect" title="Salt Lake Tribune">Salt Lake Tribune</a></i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Salt+Lake+Tribune&amp;rft.atitle=Mormon+church+traces+black+priesthood+ban+to+Brigham+Young&amp;rft.date=2013-12-16&amp;rft.aulast=Fletcher+Stack&amp;rft.aufirst=Peggy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farchive.sltrib.com%2Farticle.php%3Fid%3D57241071%26itype%3DCMSID&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Essay-116"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Essay_116-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/topics/race-and-the-priesthood?lang=eng">"Race and the Priesthood"</a>. <i>ChurchofJesusChrist.org</i>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS church">LDS church</a>. December 13, 2013. <q>Today, the Church disavows the theories advanced in the past that black skin is a sign of divine disfavor or curse, or that it reflects unrighteous actions in a premortal life; that mixed-race marriages are a sin; or that blacks or people of any other race or ethnicity are inferior in any way to anyone else. Church leaders today unequivocally condemn all racism, past and present, in any form.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=ChurchofJesusChrist.org&amp;rft.atitle=Race+and+the+Priesthood&amp;rft.date=2013-12-13&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Ftopics%2Frace-and-the-priesthood%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Skin-117"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Skin_117-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTalmage2019" class="citation journal cs1">Talmage, Jeremy (April 2019). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://scholarlypublishingcollective.org/uip/jbms/article/doi/10.5406/jbookmormstud2.28.2019.0046/275533">"Black, White, and Red All Over: Skin Color in the Book of Mormon"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Book_of_Mormon_Studies" title="Journal of Book of Mormon Studies">Journal of Book of Mormon Studies</a></i>. <b>28</b>. <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>: 46–68. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.5406%2Fjbookmormstud2.28.2019.0046">10.5406/jbookmormstud2.28.2019.0046</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.5406/jbookmormstud2.28.2019.0046">10.5406/jbookmormstud2.28.2019.0046</a>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:254312206">254312206</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Book+of+Mormon+Studies&amp;rft.atitle=Black%2C+White%2C+and+Red+All+Over%3A+Skin+Color+in+the+Book+of+Mormon&amp;rft.volume=28&amp;rft.pages=46-68&amp;rft.date=2019-04&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A254312206%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F10.5406%2Fjbookmormstud2.28.2019.0046%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.5406%2Fjbookmormstud2.28.2019.0046&amp;rft.aulast=Talmage&amp;rft.aufirst=Jeremy&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fscholarlypublishingcollective.org%2Fuip%2Fjbms%2Farticle%2Fdoi%2F10.5406%2Fjbookmormstud2.28.2019.0046%2F275533&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANative+American+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
